cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IOT, cs.SY, cs.CV. 

The paper proposes a semisupervised deep reinforcement learning model for smart city applications, specifically for indoor localization in smart buildings using Bluetooth low energy signal strength. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper focuses on developing a new learning model. The paper also utilizes variational autoencoders, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The application of the proposed model is in the context of IoT and smart city services, which suggests the category of cs.IOT (Internet of Things). The paper also involves the optimization of policies, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves image processing techniques for indoor localization, which suggests the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
